description: A spotted and torn spidersilk tablecloth covers most of the numerous dings and pockmarks on this table.  Embedded deep within the center of the table is a dagger with only the pommel and hilt visible.  Engraved on the pommel of the dagger in a spidery script is the name Hagatha, the proprietor of the tavern.
title: [Jeweled Dagger Table]
